title: MQM’s Sheikh Abdullah wins PS-117 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM), Sheikh Abdullah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-117, Karachi West-II, by securing 11,154 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Tariq Hussian, an Independent Candidate, who bagged votes 9,617.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 34.36 %.
